# Visualization of the Iris dataset

#### BASIC EXAMPLE USAGE OF DATASIST

**We use the iris data set for this sample analysis**

In \[1\]:

```text
import pandas as pd
import datasist as ds

df = pd.read_csv('iris.csv')
```

**Structdata** modules in datasist contains functions used to manipulating structured data in pandas or csv format.In \[2\]:

```text
ds.structdata.describe(df)
```

```text
cats
```

```text
['species']
```

In \[4\]:


**VISUALIZATION**

**visualization** module in datasist contains abstracted functions for making popular EDA plots without writing complex for loopsIn \[7\]:

```text
ds.visualizations.countplot(df)
```

![](data:image/png;base64,%0A)In \[8\]:

```text
ds.visualizations.boxplot(data=df, target='species')
```
